Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
partitionPushSpecialWires(25.10)              partitionPushSpecialWires(25.10)

Name
       partitionPushSpecialWires - Creates Verilog ports (connections) in par-
       titions  for  nets whose special wires overlap a partition, so that the
       special wire of the net gets pushed down when the partition command  is
       used

Syntax
       partitionPushSpecialWires

       [-help]

       [-checkOnly]

       [-keepNetName]

       {-nets <list_of_net_names> | -overlappingPartitions <ptn_names>}

       Creates  Verilog  ports (connections) in partitions for nets whose spe-
       cial wires overlap a partition, so that the special  wire  of  the  net
       gets pushed down when the partition command is used.

       Note:  For pushdown of special wires in master and clone partitions, it
       checks for the symmetry of the special  wire  shapes.  For  symmetrical
       shapes  only, the partitionPushSpecialWires command creates one port in
       the Verilog module and establishes a logical connection between the new
       port and the net of special wire  over  all  master  and  clone  hinsts
       (reuse of logical port in master and clones).

       Note: If the original net was connected to a partition port of type in-
       out,  then  an  inout  port is created inside the overlapping partition
       else only an input port is created.

Parameters
       -checkOnly
              When specified, the tool checks if the  selected  nets  special-
              wires  are  symmetric over all hints of overlapping master clone
              cells or not. In master and clone partitions, it checks for  the
              symmetry of nets and reports asymmetrical nets.

              When  the  -checkOnly parameter is not specified, the tool check
              the nets specified and creates logical ports only on valid nets.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each partitionPushSpecialWires parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man partitionPushSpecialWires

       -keepNetName
              When  specified,  it  helps  to avoid net name conflicts between
              overlapping partitions by preserving the original net name  dur-
              ing the  partitionPushSpecialWires command. It ensures that non-
              bus  nets  and  nets without a matching name in the block retain
              their names in the partition.

              Note: The partitionPushSpecialWires command creates a  partition
              port  name using the net_base_name without adding a suffix. If a
              conflict occurs, a  warning is displayed, and the name is  modi-
              fied with a suffix as per the default behavior.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -nets <list_of_net_names>
              Specifies  the  list  of  nets (Verilog nets) which have special
              wires that need to be pushed into blocks during the partitioning
              process, ensuring proper connectivity for these nets within  the
              design.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -overlappingPartitions <ptn_names>
              Specifies  the  list  of partitions and automatically identifies
              nets with special-wire routes  overlapping  with  the  specified
              partitions.  It  ensures that these special nets are pushed into
              the appropriate partitions during the partitioning process.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command checks the special  wires  of  specified
                Verilog nets n1 and creates ports on valid nets.

                partitionPushSpecialWires -nets {n1}

              * The following command checks if the special-wires of the spec-
                ified  nets are symmetric over all hints of overlapping master
                clone cells or not.

                partitionPushSpecialWires -nets {n1 n2} -checkOnly

                Report: C (mim-1) net n1 box missing in C mim-2

                Report: C (mim-1) net n1 box missing in C mim-3

                Report: C (mim-2) net n2 box missing in C mim-1

                Report: C (mim-2) net n2 box missing in C mim-3

                For pushdown, you must fix the wire asymmetry.

                After the symmetry is fixed, the following command pushes down
                symmetrical nets:

                partitionPushSpecialWires -nets {n1 n2}

                Report: user Net n1, n2 and derived nets n3 pushdown, with one
                logical port

